<subSubSection lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="15" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[667,1194,213,1759]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
DISCUSSION: 
<bibRefCitation author="Distant, W. L." box="[854,1023,1474,1496]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="329 - 462" refId="ref56527" refString="Distant, W. L. 1893. Biologia Centrali Americana: insecta, rhynchota. Hemiptera-Heteroptera Suppl., 1 - xx, 329 - 462." type="journal article" year="1893">Distant’s 1893</bibRefCitation>
description of 
<taxonomicName box="[667,880,1504,1525]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Ficinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sagittarius">
<emphasis box="[667,880,1504,1525]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Ficinus sagittarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based on 
<specimenCount box="[1024,1189,1503,1525]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="generic">six specimens</specimenCount>
, listed a variety, ‘‘var. a. Clavus and corium black and unicolorous’’. The unnamed ‘‘variety’’ was not present at the BMNH during examination, by either of us on separate occasions, of the 
<specimenCount box="[872,1107,1649,1671]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="generic" typeStatus="paralectotypes">three paralectotypes</specimenCount>
(designated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Carvalho, J. C. M. &amp; W. R. Dolling" box="[806,1181,1678,1701]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="789 - 810" refId="ref56337" refString="Carvalho, J. C. M., and W. R. Dolling. 1976. Neotropical Miridae. CCV: type designations of species described in the Biologia Centrali Americana (Hemiptera). Revista Brasileira de Biologia 36: 789 - 810." type="journal article" year="1976">Carvalho and Dolling, 1976</bibRefCitation>
). However, based on Distant’s small but revealing description ‘‘var. a’’ is conspecific
</paragraph>
<caption box="[480,898,878,897]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" startId="14.[480,518,878,897]" targetBox="[188,1166,210,847]" targetPageId="14">
<paragraph blockId="14.[480,898,878,897]" box="[480,898,878,897]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
